cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for clustering verbs with their argument types. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also makes use of low-dimensional embeddings, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with predicting sentiment and sarcasm in tweets, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
